  Source:
    Title: Letters to a Young Poet
    Locus:
      Location: Paris
      Date: February 17, 1903
  Locus:
    Daily: January 15
Title: Through All That Happens
---
As you unfold as an artist, just keep on, quietly and earnestly, growing
through all that happens to you. You cannot disrupt this process more
violently than by looking outside yourself for answers that may only be
found by attending to your innermost feeling.
